'''Headsets''' were a type of communications device worn on the head that allowed hands free communication with others, predominately by [[pilot]]s or crew among large [[starship]]s. They were generally made with either a single or double ear-piece, although some were known to cover a large area of the head of the wearer.

==History==
[[File:Obi_Wan_headset.png|thumb|left|300px|Obi-Wan Kenobi wears a Jedi headset]]
As seen as far back as the [[High Republic Era]],<ref name="HRJR">''[[The High Republic: The Great Jedi Rescue]]''</ref> virtually all [[Jedi]] used headsets to communicate with other pilots or their [[astromech droid]]s, as was the case with [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] during his [[Dogfight over Geonosis|skirmish]] with [[Jango Fett]] in [[orbit]] of the [[planet]] [[Geonosis]].<ref name="Episode II">{{Film|II}}</ref>

[[Galactic Empire|Imperial]] crewmen such as [[ensign]] [[Cauley]], a [[tactical officer]] on board the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyer]] ''[[Ultimatum]]'', wore a headset while stationed on the vessel's [[Bridge (starship)|bridge]].<ref name="AND" />

